> Our Spanish-inspired potato salad boasts crispy potatoes, briny olives, and fresh
> green beans for a salad like you've never tasted before. It's hard to compete
> with a juicy pan-seared steak, but this salad definitely gives that steak a
> run for its money.

Remove the @flank steak{2} from your fridge and allow it to come to room
temperature. Chop the @red potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel!). Place in
a #medium-sized pot{} with a generous pinch of @salt{pinch} and cover with water.
Bring to the boil on high heat, then lower the heat and cook gently for
~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{1}(halved). Trim the tops off the
@green beans{1}(trimmed) and keep to one side. Chop the @basil{1}(chopped) leaves
and the @olives{30}(chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use
a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Heat a glug of @oil{glug} in a #large frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
your green beans and cook, tossing for ~{4-6%minutes}, until soft.

> Add a splash of water every now and then to help the green beans steam and cook.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add your tomatoes to the pan and cook
for another ~{3%minutes}. Transfer your veggies to a bowl.

Wipe the pan clean and then pop back on high heat ready to cook your steak.
Season your steak with a generous pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of
@black pepper{}.

Add a glug of @oil{glug} to the pan and when the oil is very hot, add your steak
and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} on each side, until nicely browned.

> The steak will be medium-rare at this point, so if you want it cooked to medium,
> cook for 2 mins longer on each side.

Set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

While your steak rests, make your crispy potato salad. Heat a glug of
@oil{glug} in the same pan you cooked your steak in, over medium-high heat.
Add your potato to the pan and sauté for ~{4-5%minutes}, until golden-brown and
slightly crispy. Add your garlic and basil leaves and cook for ~{30%seconds}
more.

Season your potato with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Stir in your olives, veggies
and @balsamic vinegar{1} and cook for another ~{1%minute}, until warmed through.

Slice your steak against the grain and serve alongside your crispy potato salad.
Drizzle over any juices from your pan. Enjoy!